article.headline: William & Mary 86, James Madison 68
article.story: WILLIAMSBURG, Va. (AP) -- Corey Cofield scored 17 points and had six rebounds Saturday to lead William & Mary to a 86-68 victory over James Madison in a battle of winless teams in the Colonial Athletic Association. Calvin Baker also scored 17 for the Tribe (6-13, 1-9 CAA), including five out of seven three-pointers. Peter Stein added 16 points and Taylor Mokris had 13. William & Mary was 23-for-27 from the foul line, James Madison just 8-for-15. The Tribe took the lead for good when baker's 3-pointer made it 27-25 with 5:34 left in the first half. James Madison (3-15, 0-10) was down by 13 at the break and could get no closer than 11 points at the 13:05 mark in the second half. Ray Barbosa scored 18 points and Juwann James had 16 for the Dukes.
